Look around you. Take it all in. It's not every day someone gets to be in a kitchen.

You rest your hand against a wall, but you miss the wall and fall onto a fridge. Is this what you came to TextWorld for? This... fridge? The fridge contains a sliced white onion and a red onion. Suddenly, you bump your head on the ceiling, but it's not such a bad bump that it's going to prevent you from looking at objects and even things. You see a counter. The counter is vast. But there isn't a thing on it. You can see a stove. You wonder idly who left that here. The stove is conventional. But the thing is empty. What, you think everything in TextWorld should have stuff on it?

There is an open frosted-glass door leading east. There is an open screen door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going south, that entranceway is not blocked by one. There is an exit to the west.

Suddenly, you bump your head on the ceiling, but it's not such a bad bump that it's going to prevent you from looking at objects and even things. You see a counter. The counter is vast. But there isn't a thing on it. You can see a stove. You wonder idly who left that here. The stove is conventional. But the thing is empty. What, you think everything in TextWorld should have stuff on it?

There is an open frosted-glass door leading east. There is an open screen door leading north. You don't like doors? Why not try going south, that entranceway is not blocked by one. There is an exit to the west.
